  "message": "chore: regenerate internal checksums and fix test script permissions\n\nscripts/generated/internal_checksums.sh:\n- Update SHA256 hashes for scripts/lib/update.sh and scripts/acfs-update\n  to reflect upstream changes to those files. These checksums are used\n  by the ACFS self-integrity verification system to detect tampering\n  or drift in distributed installer scripts.\n\nscripts/test_ntm_palette.sh:\n- Add executable permission (chmod +x) so the test script can be\n  invoked directly without explicitly calling `bash test_ntm_palette.sh`.\n  This was likely an oversight from when the file was first created.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
